  "elapsed_s": 3.7,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 37,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "But again, coming back to the Schutzhaft, I was always, at that time or before, it was still the impression that he was kind-- in protective custody. 'Schutzhaft' means 'under schutz'-- 'protected'-- by the Nazis.",
      "word_count": 35
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 37,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "But at that time, it was already clear that these things like concentration camps, where people are dying, is happening.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 37,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "I did not know about all the places where it occurred.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 37,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "But I knew that it occurred with my father.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 37,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And later on I became aware also that-- what happened to my mother and my-- my-- my sisters.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 37,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And I obtained documentation in Israel about my mother.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 37,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And they wrote me, and I have it and framed, even, that my mother and three sisters were-- [GERMAN]-- which means '1902,' in Vizhnitz, and her children-- [GERMAN]-- Miriam Habergrutz, Rosa Habergrutz, Mendel Habergrutz, [GERMAN]-- when they're-- they're born.",
      "word_count": 39
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 37,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "[GERMAN]-- on 21st of January, 1942, to Riga deportiert.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 37,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "They were deported to Riga.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 37,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "And since there was no sign of life after that, so we can take-- take it as assurance-- 'Sicherheit'-- we can take it as assurance that they are not anymore alive and that they were-- [GERMAN]-- that their-- that their life does not exist anymore.",
      "word_count": 45
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 37,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "And this was my mother and sister-- sisters.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 37,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "And my grandmother was at a later date also deported, but to another place, which was Belzec in Poland, in Lublin, near Lublin, in Poland.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 37,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "And this happened to [GERMAN] that Mrs.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 37,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "Hannah [NON-ENGLISH] [GERMAN] [NON-ENGLISH] [GERMAN] on 30th-- on the 30th of August in 1875 in Vizhnitz, which is also in Poland.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 37,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "In-- on 10th of May in 1942, [GERMAN]-- to-- where was deported to [NON-ENGLISH].",
      "word_count": 14
    }
  ],
